ru-abbrev of:

{{abbreviation of|lang=ru|{{{1|}}}|{{{2|}}}|{{{3|}}}|tr={{{tr|}}}|dot={{{dot|}}}|nocap={{#if:{{{cap|}}}||1}}}}<!--
--><noinclude>{{documentation}}</noinclude>

ru-abbrev of/documentation:

{{documentation subpage}}
==Usage==
This template is used to properly format a Russian [[abbreviation]]. The word or words may or may not have direct or indirect links. If a term does not exist in Wiktionary and is not an appropriate entry, the link may go to Wikipedia. The following parameters exist:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Description !! Notes
|-
| <code>1</code> || if {{para|2}} is empty, {{para|1}} is what the abbreviation stands for, as it is to be displayed, with the page link automatically derived from it; else, it is the page to link to, with the display form specified separately in {{para|2}} || normally required
|-
| <code>2</code> || see comments for {{para|1}} || normally omitted
|-
| <code>3</code> || English-language gloss || optional
|-
| <code>tr</code> || Manual transliteration || normally omitted, defaulting to the automatic transliteration of the display form
|-
| <code>cap</code> || If non-empty, capitalize the first letter of ''abbreviation'' || normally omitted
|-
| <code>dot</code> || If non-empty, punctuation to emit after the rest of the template || normally omitted, and no punctuation will be emitted
|}

The page is automatically placed in the category [[:Category:Russian abbreviations]].

;Examples:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Word !! Kode !! Result !! Notes
|-
| {{m|ru|а́ва}} || <code><nowiki>{{ru-abbrev of|авата́р||[[avatar]]}}</nowiki></code> || {{ru-abbrev of|авата́р||[[avatar]]}} || links to the page named ''аватар'' (accents automatically stripped)
|-
|{{m|ru|Ж}} || <code><nowiki>{{ru-abbrev of|[[женский|же́нская]] [[убо́рная]]||women's restroom}}: [[ladies' room]], women's [[toilet]]</nowiki></code> || {{ru-abbrev of|[[женский|же́нская]] [[убо́рная]]||women's restroom}}: [[ladies' room]], women's [[toilet]] || link to individual words (a bare link like <code><nowiki>[[убо́рная]]</nowiki></code> is automatically accent-stripped to produce a link to the page named ''уборная''); note literal meaning using the gloss param, and fluent definition following the template
|}
<includeonly>
[[Category:Russian definition-line templates]]
</includeonly>

ru-acronym of:

{{acronym of|lang=ru|{{{1|}}}|{{{2|}}}|{{{3|}}}|tr={{{tr|}}}|dot={{{dot|}}}|nocap={{#if:{{{cap|}}}||1}}}}<!--
