==Usage==
This template is used to properly format a Russian [[initialism]]. The word or words may or may not have direct or indirect links. If a term does not exist in Wiktionary and is not an appropriate entry, the link may go to Wikipedia. The following parameters exist:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Description !! Notes
|-
| <code>1</code> || if {{para|2}} is empty, {{para|1}} is what the initialism stands for, as it is to be displayed, with the page link automatically derived from it; else, it is the page to link to, with the display form specified separately in {{para|2}} || normally required
|-
| <code>2</code> || see comments for {{para|1}} || normally omitted
|-
| <code>3</code> || English-language gloss || optional
|-
| <code>tr</code> || Manual transliteration || normally omitted, defaulting to the automatic transliteration of the display form
|-
