ru-etym abbrev of/documentation:

{{documentation subpage}}
==Usage==
This template is used to properly format a Russian [[abbreviation]] in an etymology section. The word or words may or may not have direct or indirect links. If a term does not exist in Wiktionary and is not an appropriate entry, the link may go to Wikipedia. The following parameters exist:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Description !! Notes
|-
| <code>1</code> || if {{para|2}} is empty, {{para|1}} is what the abbreviation stands for, as it is to be displayed, with the page link automatically derived from it; else, it is the page to link to, with the display form specified separately in {{para|2}} || normally required
|-
| <code>2</code> || see comments for {{para|1}} || normally omitted
|-
| <code>3</code> || English-language gloss || optional
|-
| <code>tr</code> || Manual transliteration || normally omitted, defaulting to the automatic transliteration of the display form
|-
| <code>nocap</code> || If non-empty, don't capitalize the first letter of ''Abbreviation'' || normally omitted
|}

The page is automatically placed in the category [[:Category:Russian abbreviations]].

;Examples:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Word !! Kode !! Result !! Notes
|-
| {{m|ru|зав}} || <code><nowiki>{{ru-etym abbrev of|заве́дующий}}.</nowiki></code> || {{ru-etym abbrev of|заве́дующий}}. || links to the page named ''заведующий'' (accents automatically stripped)
|-
| {{m|ru|вещмешо́к}} || <code><nowiki>{{ru-etym abbrev of|[[вещево́й]] [[мешо́к]]||clothing sack, duffel bag}}.</nowiki></code> || {{ru-etym abbrev of|[[вещево́й]] [[мешо́к]]||clothing sack, duffel bag}}. || link to individual words (a bare link like <code><nowiki>[[мешо́к]]</nowiki></code> is automatically accent-stripped to produce a link to the page named ''мешок'')
|}
